If he rejects the historical evidence for H-bomb explosions, then there is really no hope for him, since these are as well documented and as certain as the names of American Presidents. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://nuketesting.enviroweb.org/hew/Nwfaq/Nfaq0.html">FAS nuke FAQ</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> has plenty of links to this kind of information, and any encyclopedia will also have the relevant history.<br>
Let me guess, he doesn't believe that the moon landings were real, either?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/unuclearharbinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nuclear Harbinger</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ditl.org/Gengrafix/smallcomspin.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/22/02 4:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stupid roommate</span><hr size=1> hey man i know what ya meen. some dudes won't beleave anything<br>
no matter what yer evidence. maybe he needs to watch more <br>
