prove yer point? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ubrp17.showPublicProfile?language=EN>brp17</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/22/02 7:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Well...</span><hr size=1> I don't think it's conspiricies, he doesn't believe in conspiricies... I really just don't know what he's thinking. I tried to understand that, but he told me to drop the issue. I tried telling him pretty much everything mentioned, but he wants hard evidence, and I'm of more than half a mind to just print some web site, stick it somewhere where he has a fair chance of noticing it, but not too much, and leave it at that. He's really mad at me, won't even talk to me (So much for a small discussion, isn't it...) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nebobgrenville>nebobgrenville</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://my.oregonstate.edu/courses/1/NE_114_X001_F2002/uploads/homepage/_1060577_1/triga.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/23/02 5:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Well...</span><hr size=1> Sounds a lot like a guy I argued with once who believed that antimatter has never been produced and if it is, it will create a chain reaction which will destroy the universe. People don't like to feel ignorant, particularly if they are. <p>&quot;If,&quot; he wispered, &quot;if we could only pick that lock....&quot; - , THE WORLD SET FREE</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dustyslaunchpad>Dustys Launchpad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/24/02 1:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Atmospheric Conflagration</span><hr size=1> I think your room-mate has read about Edward Teller's concern about the Trinity test and misunderstood it.<br>
<br>
Teller calculated that there was a 1 in a 1,000,000 chance that the (Atomic) detonation would provide enough energy to start a self sustaining chemical reaction between the atmospheric Nitrogen and Oxygen that could consume the entire atmosphere.<br>
<br>
This was a one off risk, the fact that it didn't happen means it will *never* happen. But at the time I think that, WW2 not withstanding, they were probably mad to do it given this level of risk. A reactor blowing up is one thing, destroying the entire planet is another altogether! I guess we were lucky.<br>
<br>
Dusty <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1280<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/26/02 9:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Atmospheric Conflagration</span><hr size=1> I wonder if some struggling alien civilization on a distant<br>
world halted all nuclear bomb development because of that risk...?<br>
<br>
Would they ever be able to imagine an Orion?<br>
